# The REAL backend is the default. `npm run dev` proxies same-origin /api calls to the Spring
# backend (VITE_PROXY_TARGET, default http://localhost:8080) — start that backend on :8080 first.
#
# To develop backend-free with the in-browser MSW mocks instead, use `npm run dev:mock`
# (loads .env.mock):
#   VITE_USE_MSW=true            # turn the mock worker on
#
# VITE_PROXY_TARGET overrides where the dev server proxies /api (no CORS in the browser):
#   VITE_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:8080
#
# VITE_API_URL only needs setting for a direct (non-proxied) absolute backend origin, which
# then requires the backend to send CORS headers. Leave empty for the proxy setup.
# VITE_API_URL=
